Vietnam Stock Movers: Hau Giang Pharma, Kinh Do, PVI Holdings

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-08-17T04:45:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-17/vietnam-stock-movers-hau-giang-pharma-kinh-do-pvi-holdings.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in  Vietnam  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the 11 a.m. local-time close.  The VN Index, the benchmark measure of the Ho Chi Minh City
Stock Exchange, rose 1.8 percent to 393.46.  Hau Giang Pharmaceutical Joint-Stock Co. (DHG VN),
Vietnam’s biggest publicly traded drugmaker, gained 2.5 percent
to 60,500 dong, the highest since July 28. The company plans to
pay its shareholders a dividend of 3,000 dong a share on Sept.
16, according to a statement on the bourse’s website.  Kinh Do Corp. (KDC)  , a Vietnamese producer of baked
goods and candy, increased 3.8 percent to 32,500 dong, the
highest close since July 12. The company will pay its
shareholders a dividend of 1,200 dong on Oct. 19, it said in a
statement on the exchange’s website.  PVI Holdings (PVI VN), Vietnam’s second-largest listed
insurer, rose 5.1 percent to 16,400 dong, the most since Aug.
10. The company will sell a 25 percent stake to  Germany ’s Talanx
AG, Chief Executive Officer Bui Van Thuan said by phone today
from Hanoi.  Thuan declined to give a value for the sale. The agreement
will be completed today, he said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Darren Boey at 
 dboey@bloomberg.net  